1) After you have created your account, set up a free "Shared Cluster" then choose your preferred cloud provider and region.

2) By default, MongoDB Atlas is completely locked down and has no external access.

3) You will need to set up a user and add your IP address to the list of allowed IP addresses.

4) Under "Database Access", create a new user and keep track of the username and password.

5) Next, under "Network Access", add your current IP address to allow access from your computer.
